result.execSummary:
The defendant Travis P McNamar was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Expose Child to Harmful Material, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.11(2)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Defendant was ordered to report immediately to the probation and parole office.

miscConds.notes: Fees, surcharges and costs to be paid on a schedule established by the agent.  Defendant is ordered to pay the $250.00 DNA surcharge, provide a sample for testing through the Dept. of Corrections as required in felony convictions.

Defendant shall attend counseling, treatments, programming, evaluations as deemed appropriate by the agent releasing all records to the agent upon request.  Defendant to submit to sex offender assessment and counseling, releasing all records to his agent.

The defendant shall have no contact with anyone under the age of 18 of any kind, whether direct or indirect, including in person, in writing, by phone, by e-mail or other electronic means, through a third party or in any other way.  Exception for immediate family members, he may have contact with secondary family members, such as cousins, with someone over the age of 25 supervising, or incidental contact, all with the approval of his agent.    
Defendant shall have no use of the Internet unless for education and/or employment purposes and must be approved by his agent.

The defendant shall pay Department of Correction fees as directed by the agent.
Defendant is to comply with Sex Offender Registry Program as required and comply with DOC Sex Offender Rules of Supervision.  .

timeConds.notes: Defendant granted 234 days credit for time served.
